"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The metric function passed to DBSCAN should take two arrays from X as input and return a value indicating the distance between them. However, in this code, the get_point_distance function is not being used correctly because it expects two points as input but the DBSCAN algorithm will pass two arrays of points to the metric function.\",\n  \"patch\": \"28c28\\n< clustering = DBSCAN(metric=get_point_distance).fit(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\\n---\\n> clustering = DBSCAN(metric=lambda x, y: euclidean_distances(x, y)).fit(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\\n\"\n}"